-- Pablo Martin Wins Golf's Alfred Dunhill Title for the Second Straight Year
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-12-12T15:11:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/pablo-martin-wins-golf-s-alfred-dunhill-title-for-the-second-straight-year.html
Pablo Martin scored a final-round
70, 2-under par, today to win golf’s Alfred Dunhill Championship
for the second straight year.  The Spaniard finished on 11-under, two shots ahead of South
African duo Anthony Michael and Charl Schwartzel and Denmark’s
Thorbjorn Olesen, at the Leopard Creek Country Club in Malelane,
South Africa.  The winner picked up a check for 158,500 euros ($210,000).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  